The idea is to make plant knowledge easy to access â€” even offline â€” and to bring together both folk wisdom and modern herbal information in one place.

ğŸª´ What Iâ€™m building

Right now, the app is being shaped piece by piece.
The mobile version will be made with React Native, and the plant data comes from a JSON file I maintain separately (which I am most likely going to switch to SQLite later).
For now, that data is managed using a smaller helper tool I built myself â€” Herb Editor Lite.

ğŸ§° Herb Editor Lite (tool)

This is the offline HTML tool that I use to build and organize all the herb data.
It helps me add new herbs, edit bilingual descriptions, attach recipes, mark toxicity, and manage the overall structure before the data is imported into the mobile app.

You can find it under:
tools/herb-editor-lite/

